rComments: Laura is a wonderful professor and the class was great. She is very helpful in answering any questions about readings, essays, etc. Attendance is key as well as textbooks, but still I looked forward to her class each week because we would talk about current issues and not just what was in our Core books!

Laura talks in a monotone voice which can bore you but overall she is a good professor. She grades fairly and addresses your questions clearly through email. I'll agree that the extra section was not very helpful.

Laura is maybe one of the meh english professor out there. She makes you do too much, such as extra mandatory section, and the class does not help to improve your writing. We discussed the same topic for 2 weeks and fell behind. Also she grades hard and only helps if u go to office hours.

WARNING DO NOT TAKE HER CLAS!!!! She is teh hardest teacher out there. Out of all the core classes in College 10 she makes you do so much extra work that it is ridiculous. She makes you attend extra sections and give you extra homework that it takes too much priority. Her office hours, waste of time. She rarely helps. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS!!!!

Laura is an incredibly knowledgable person who is more than willing to discuss anything you have a question about. I've had her as a TA and a professor and both experiences were very rewarding. This class was exceptionally interesting, I'd recommend it to anyone even remotely interested in the history of urban development.
Laura is a pretty good teacher but her grading can be weird.
